modules.description: This module provides operations for constructing, validating, and serializing cron entries using field-level components like `minute`, `hour`, and `day_of_month`, along with composite types such as `Cron.entry` and `Cron.t` representing individual jobs and crontabs. It supports parsing and formatting cron expressions in POSIX format, inspecting time constraints via `validator`, and managing user-specific crontabs through system integration. Use cases include programmatically scheduling recurring tasks, validating cron syntax, and dynamically modifying crontab entries without manual file editing.
